<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8" />
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />

<title>Proteomics | PanorOmics</title>

<style>
*{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box}

body{
  background:#020817;
  color:white;
  font-family:Inter,Arial,sans-serif;
  overflow-x:hidden;
}

.page{
  padding:72px 7% 42px;
}

.back{
  color:#3b82f6;
  text-decoration:none;
  font-size:.92rem;
  font-weight:700;
}

.hero{
  margin-top:34px;
  display:grid;
  grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;
  gap:34px;
  align-items:center;
}

h1{
  font-size:clamp(2.3rem,4vw,4rem);
  line-height:.98;
  letter-spacing:-.05em;
}

h1 span{
  color:#3b82f6;
}

p{
  margin-top:18px;
  color:#cbd5e1;
  font-size:.95rem;
  line-height:1.65;
  max-width:680px;
}

.video-box,
.image-box{
  border-radius:22px;
  overflow:hidden;
  border:1px solid rgba(59,130,246,.14);
  box-shadow:0 0 50px rgba(37,99,235,.12);
}

video,img{
  width:100%;
  display:block;
}

.section{
  padding:38px 0;
}

h2{
  font-size:clamp(1.7rem,3vw,2.6rem);
  margin-bottom:18px;
}

h2 span{
  color:#3b82f6;
}

.grid{
  display:grid;
  grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(230px,1fr));
  gap:18px;
  margin-top:24px;
}

.card{
  background:rgba(8,15,35,.72);
  border:1px solid rgba(59,130,246,.12);
  border-radius:20px;
  padding:20px;
}

.card h3{
  color:#3b82f6;
  margin-bottom:10px;
  font-size:1.1rem;
}

.card p{
  margin-top:0;
  font-size:.9rem;
  color:#94a3b8;
}

@media(max-width:900px){

  .hero{
    grid-template-columns:1fr
  }

  .page{
    padding:64px 20px 36px
  }
}
</style>
</head>

<body>

<main class="page">

  <a class="back" href="/">← Back to PanorOmics</a>

  <section class="hero">

    <div>

      <h1>Proteomics: <span>The Functional Landscape of Life</span></h1>

      <p>
        Proteomics investigates the complete set of proteins expressed within
        biological systems. By studying protein abundance, structure,
        interactions, signaling pathways, and post-translational modifications,
        proteomics reveals the functional machinery driving cellular biology,
        disease mechanisms, and therapeutic discovery.
      </p>

    </div>

    <div class="video-box">

      <video autoplay muted loop playsinline>

        <source
          src="/Proteomics Functional biology.mp4"
          type="video/mp4"
        />

      </video>

    </div>

  </section>

  <section class="section">

    <h2>What is <span>Proteomics?</span></h2>

    <div class="image-box">

      <img
        src="/1_Proteomics.png"
        alt="Proteomics overview infographic"
      />

    </div>

  </section>

  <section class="section">

    <h2>Core Areas</h2>

    <div class="grid">

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Protein Identification</h3>
        <p>Characterizing proteins and their biological roles.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Mass Spectrometry</h3>
        <p>Profiling proteins through LC-MS/MS technologies.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Protein Interactions</h3>
        <p>Understanding signaling networks and molecular complexes.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Post-translational Modifications</h3>
        <p>Studying phosphorylation, acetylation, ubiquitination, and PTMs.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Biomarker Discovery</h3>
        <p>Identifying disease-associated proteins for diagnosis and therapy.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Systems Proteomics</h3>
        <p>Integrating proteomics with genomics and multi-omics systems biology.</p>
      </div>

    </div>

  </section>

</main>

</body>
</html>
